        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 13 at 5:31PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 531 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 15
miles northeast of Many, or 15 miles west of Natchitoches, moving
southeast at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Allen, Robeline, Powhatan, Hagewood and Marthaville.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
